{"id":10722,"date":"2012-12-27T21:56:47","date_gmt":"2012-12-28T02:56:47","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=10722"},"modified":"2019-05-20T15:14:15","modified_gmt":"2019-05-20T11:14:15","slug":"madinah-city-prophet","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/12\/27\/madinah-city-prophet\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Madinah: The Prophet&#8217;s city of Medina is sacred ground"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ali ibn Abi Talib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>Medina is sacred from the mountain unto the end. Whoever innovates a heresy in it or aids a heretic, upon him is the curse of Allah, the angels, and the people altogether. His obligatory and surplus good deeds will not be accepted<\/b>.\u00a0<b>The protection of the Muslims is one. Whoever betrays a Muslim, upon him is the curse of Allah, the angels, and the people altogether. His obligatory and surplus good deeds will not be accepted.<\/b>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1771, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1370<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/strong><\/em>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u064d\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e<b>\u00a0\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e\u0629\u064f \u062d\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0645\u064c \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\